        "title": "Improve Antigravity quota detection",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR improves Antigravity usage detection and display so CodexBar reflects Antigravity’s current quota model.\r\n\r\nAntigravity quotas are now shown as two shared model pools:\r\n\r\n1. Gemini Session\r\n2. Gemini Weekly\r\n3. Claude + GPT Session\r\n4. Claude + GPT Weekly\r\n\r\nThe session row corresponds to Antigravity’s 5-hour limit.\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\n- Prefer richer local Antigravity sources in this order:\r\n  - Antigravity 2.0 app\r\n  - `agy` CLI\r\n  - Antigravity IDE\r\n  - Google OAuth when account-scoped OAuth is available\r\n- Add parsing for Antigravity’s `RetrieveUserQuotaSummary` endpoint.\r\n- Normalize Antigravity quota groups into `Gemini` and `Claude + GPT`.\r\n- Rename the 5-hour limit to `Session`.\r\n- Keep legacy model-quota fallback behavior when the full quota summary is unavailable.\r\n- Keep the OAuth generic Gemini fallback behavior.\r\n- Improve local app/IDE/CLI process detection.\r\n- Update menu, widget, highest-usage, and diagnostic behavior for Antigravity quota-summary rows.\r\n- Add focused tests for parser, source ordering, local probing, OAuth fallback, menu rendering, widget rendering, and account cleanup.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nThe Antigravity IDE may still expose less quota information than the Antigravity 2.0 app. When the full quota summary endpoint is unavailable, CodexBar falls back to the older model/session quota data instead of inventing weekly rows.\r\n\r\n## Manual Proof\r\n\r\nAttached screenshot shows the expected Antigravity menu output:\r\n\r\n- Gemini Session\r\n- Gemini Weekly\r\n- Claude + GPT Session\r\n- Claude + GPT Weekly\r\n<img width=\"295\" height=\"248\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-13 at 22 28 11\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3c6085b2-9f63-4104-955d-8c5e2ffc7868\" />\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n\r\n- `swift test --filter 'AntigravityQuotaSummaryTests|AntigravityStatusProbeTests|AntigravityCLIHTTPSFetchStrategyTests|AntigravityCLISessionTests|AntigravityRemoteUsageFetcherTests|MenuCardAntigravityTests|UsageStoreWidgetSnapshotTests|SettingsStoreCoverageTests|CodexBarWidgetProviderTests|ProviderSettingsDescriptorTests|ProviderDiagnosticExportTests'`\r\n  - Passed: 251 tests\r\n- `make check`\r\n  - Passed with 0 lint violations",
